{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"timeoutAddSecondsFull"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"priority"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"interval"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"function"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSourceFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GDestroyNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The function is called repeatedly until it returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_SOURCE_REMOVE"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", at which point the timeout is automatically destroyed and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the function will not be called again."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_timeout_add()"},{"type":"text","text":", this function operates at whole second granularity."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The initial starting point of the timer is determined by the implementation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the implementation is expected to group multiple timers together so that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"they fire all at the same time. To allow this grouping, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"},{"type":"text","text":" to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"first timer is rounded and can deviate up to one second from the specified"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interval. Subsequent timer iterations will generally run at the specified"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interval."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that timeout functions may be delayed, due to the processing of other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"event sources. Thus they should not be relied on for precise timing."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"After each call to the timeout function, the time of the next"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"timeout is recalculated based on the current time and the given "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interval"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"#mainloop-memory-management"},{"type":"text","text":" for details"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"data"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want timing more precise than whole seconds, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_timeout_add()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The grouping of timers to fire at the same time results in a more power"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and CPU efficient behavior so if your timer is in multiples of seconds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and you donâ€™t require the first timer exactly one second from now, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_timeout_add_seconds()"},{"type":"text","text":" is preferred over "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_timeout_add()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This internally creates a main loop source using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_timeout_source_new_seconds()"},{"type":"text","text":" and attaches it to the main loop context"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_source_attach()"},{"type":"text","text":". You can do these steps manually if you need"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"greater control."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is safe to call this function from any thread."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time.  See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_get_monotonic_time()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timeoutaddsecondsfull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/timeoutAddSecondsFull(priority:interval:function:data:notify:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets a function to be called at regular intervals, with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"priority"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier",